{
  "texts": [
    "We choose a small number of candidate values for each parameter, and then carry out a back-test for each combination, evaluating multiple performance metrics.",
    "Of course this is practical only when we are choosing just a few parameters, and we consider only a few candidate values for each one.",
    "Gridding is often carried out with a first crude parameter gridding, with the candidate values spaced by a factor of ten or so; then, when good values of these parameters are found, a more refined grid search is used to focus in on parameters near the good ones found in the first crude search.",
    "In any case there is no reason to find or specify parameter values very accurately; specifying them to even 10% is not needed.",
    "For one thing, the back-test itself is only an approximation."
  ]
}